            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Hmm. It's easy for the bytes case because the lifetime of the pointer is tied to the bytes object owning the data. I guess it's similar for the memoryview where the pointer would be tied to the lifetime of the view (not the buffer owner).\n\nOTOH, we already have `s = &b[0]` which is commonly used. I consider it less obvious than a simple assignment, although once you know it, it's not difficult to remember. If we allow simple assignments, we'd have two ways to do it. Not sure if that's necessary.",
